{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/Interview_Prep/Interview_Cake/3_bit_manipulation/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<blockquote>\n<p>Interview Cake의 Bit Manipulation 정리</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3>Binary Numbers</h3>\n<p>computers use binary number system (0, 1)</p>\n<h4>Unsigned Binary Numbers</h4>\n<p>use plain old base 2</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; [object Object] max-width: 227px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 86.78414096916299%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"3 base2\" title=\"3 base2\" src=\"/static/a2b59fd57050c875bfbd95bbaf657609/87a7e/3_base2.png\" srcset=\"/static/a2b59fd57050c875bfbd95bbaf657609/00d96/3_base2.png 148w,\n/static/a2b59fd57050c875bfbd95bbaf657609/87a7e/3_base2.png 227w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 227px) 100vw, 227px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<h4>Signed Binary Numbers</h4>\n<p>use <strong>2's complement</strong> encoding to represent both negative and positive numbers</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; [object Object] max-width: 238px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 85.71428571428571%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"3 twos complement\" title=\"3 twos complement\" src=\"/static/b487905eae76a9de55e84ae9d8cbf7d9/55fcc/3_twos_complement.png\" srcset=\"/static/b487905eae76a9de55e84ae9d8cbf7d9/00d96/3_twos_complement.png 148w,\n/static/b487905eae76a9de55e84ae9d8cbf7d9/55fcc/3_twos_complement.png 238w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 238px) 100vw, 238px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<ul>\n<li>the leftmost digit indicates positive (0) or negative (1)</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>advantages</strong>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>there is only way to represent zero (= sequence of only 0s)</li>\n<li>base operations (+, -, *) are the same regardless of whether numbers are positive or negative</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>if asked to convert binary into decimal or vice-versa (convert decimal to binary), ask <strong>\"is that in two's complement or not?\"</strong></p>\n<h3>Bitwise Operations</h3>\n<h4>AND ( &#x26; )</h4>\n<p>return <strong>1 if both bits are 1</strong>; otherwise returns 0</p>\n<pre class=\"andromeda vscode-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><code class=\"vscode-highlight-code\"><span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk6\">5</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">6</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // = 4</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">101</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">110</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // = 0100 (4)</span></span></code></pre>\n<h4>OR ( | )</h4>\n<p>returns <strong>1 if at least one bit is 1</strong>; otherwise returns 0</p>\n<pre class=\"andromeda vscode-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><code class=\"vscode-highlight-code\"><span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk6\">5</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">|</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">6</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // = 7</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">101</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">110</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // = 0111 (7)</span></span></code></pre>\n<h4>XOR ( ^ )</h4>\n<p>returns <strong>1 if exactly one of the bits is 1</strong>; otherwise returns 0</p>\n<pre class=\"andromeda vscode-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><code class=\"vscode-highlight-code\"><span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk6\">5</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">^</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">6</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // = 3</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">101</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">^</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">110</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // = 0011 (3)</span></span></code></pre>\n<h4>NOT ( ~ )</h4>\n<p><strong>reverses the bits</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"andromeda vscode-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><code class=\"vscode-highlight-code\"><span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk5\">~</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">5</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // = -6 in 2&#39;s complement</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk5\">~</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">101</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // = 1010 (-6)</span></span></code></pre>\n<h3>Bit Shifting</h3>\n<p>bit shift moves each digit the binary number to the left or right</p>\n<h4>Left Shifts ( &#x3C;&#x3C; )</h4>\n<p>means <strong>multiplying the number by the power of 2s</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"andromeda vscode-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><code class=\"vscode-highlight-code\"><span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk4\">// lose leftmost bits and insert 0s on the right end</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">010</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">&lt;&lt;</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">1</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // 0100</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">010</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">&lt;&lt;</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">2</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // 1000</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk4\">// 0010 (2) &lt;&lt; 2 = 1000 (8)</span></span></code></pre>\n<h4>Right Shifts ( >> )</h4>\n<p>languages handle arithmetic and logical right shifting in different ways. Most C++ compilers implement <strong>logical right shifting on unsigned types</strong> and <strong>arithmetic right shifting on signed types</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Logical Right Shifts</strong>: means <strong>dividing integers by power of 2s</strong> (throw away remainders)</p>\n<pre class=\"andromeda vscode-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><code class=\"vscode-highlight-code\"><span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk4\">// lose rightmost bits and insert 0s on the left end</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk6\">1011</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">1</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // 0101</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk6\">1011</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">3</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // 0001</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk4\">// 0101 (5) &gt;&gt; 1 = 0010 (2)</span></span></code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Arithmetic Right Shifts</strong>: can <strong>preserve number's sign</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"andromeda vscode-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><code class=\"vscode-highlight-code\"><span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk4\">// lose rightmost bits and extend left end</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk6\">1011</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">1</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // 0101</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk9\">0</span><span class=\"mtk6\">011</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk5\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"mtk1\"> </span><span class=\"mtk6\">2</span><span class=\"mtk4\"> // 0000</span></span>\n<span class=\"vscode-highlight-line\"><span class=\"mtk4\">// 0010 (2) &lt;&lt; 2 = 1000 (8)</span></span></code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Integer Overflow</h3>\n<p>the variable's value > computer's allocated memory</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>sextrillion (= a billion trillion; 70 bits) can't fit in modern computers 64 bits</li>\n<li>result of multiplication can't fit in 64 bits</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Handling Integer Overflows</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>C++ or Java: processor will throw out the bits that don't fit</li>\n<li>Python: will automatically allocate space for larger number</li>\n<li>Swift: throw an error</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Prevent Integer Overflow</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>C++: reduce likelihood by using larger integer types</li>\n<li>use overflow-checking features provided by compiler or interpreter</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<style class=\"vscode-highlight-styles\">\n  :root {\n  --vscode-highlight-padding-v: 1rem;\n  --vscode-highlight-padding-h: 1.5rem;\n  --vscode-highlight-padding-top: var(--vscode-highlight-padding-v);\n  --vscode-highlight-padding-right: var(--vscode-highlight-padding-h);\n  --vscode-highlight-padding-bottom: var(--vscode-highlight-padding-v);\n  --vscode-highlight-padding-left: var(--vscode-highlight-padding-h);\n  --vscode-highlight-border-radius: 8px;\n\n  --vscode-highlight-line-highlighted-background-color: transparent;\n  --vscode-highlight-line-highlighted-border-width: 4px;\n  --vscode-highlight-line-highlighted-border-color: transparent;\n}\n\n.vscode-highlight {\n  overflow: auto;\n  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;\n  padding-top: 1rem;\n  padding-top: var(--vscode-highlight-padding-top);\n  padding-bottom: 1rem;\n  padding-bottom: var(--vscode-highlight-padding-bottom);\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  border-radius: var(--vscode-highlight-border-radius);\n  font-feature-settings: normal;\n}\n\n.vscode-highlight-code {\n  display: inline-block;\n  min-width: 100%;\n}\n\n.vscode-highlight-line {\n  display: inline-block;\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n  width: 100%;\n  padding-left: 1.5rem;\n  padding-left: var(--vscode-highlight-padding-left);\n  padding-right: 1.5rem;\n  padding-right: var(--vscode-highlight-padding-right);\n}\n\n.vscode-highlight-line-highlighted {\n  background-color: var(--vscode-highlight-line-highlighted-background-color);\n  box-shadow: inset var(--vscode-highlight-line-highlighted-border-width) 0 0 0 var(--vscode-highlight-line-highlighted-border-color);\n}\n\n  .andromeda {\nbackground-color: #23262E;\ncolor: #D5CED9;\n}\n\n.andromeda .mtk1 { color: #D5CED9; }\n.andromeda .mtk2 { color: #23262E; }\n.andromeda .mtk3 { color: #00E8C6; }\n.andromeda .mtk4 { color: #5F6167; }\n.andromeda .mtk5 { color: #EE5D43; }\n.andromeda .mtk6 { color: #F39C12; }\n.andromeda .mtk7 { color: #FFE66D; }\n.andromeda .mtk8 { color: #F92672; }\n.andromeda .mtk9 { color: #C74DED; }\n.andromeda .mtk10 { color: #7CB7FF; }\n.andromeda .mtk11 { color: #FF00AA; }\n.andromeda .mtk12 { color: #96E072; }\n.andromeda .mtki { font-style: italic; }\n.andromeda .mtkb { font-weight: bold; }\n.andromeda .mtku { text-decoration: underline; text-underline-position: under; }\n</style>","frontmatter":{"title":"Interview Cake - 3. Bit Manipulation","date":"2019-07-15","tags":["Interview Cake","Bit"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Interview_Prep/Interview_Cake/3_bit_manipulation/"}}}